title.narrative: Children and young people in humanitarian situations have access to protective, quality basic education services

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, a total of 618,174 children and young people (260,822 girls) have access to protective quality education services, representing 84.7% of the target. The increase in both enrolment and demand, contributed to reducing the number of out-of-school children (OOSC), with other OOSC supported through the establishment and rehabilitation of 322 safe and protective Temporary Learning Spaces (TLSs). UNICEF supported the training of 1,466 teachers (410 female) through Continuous Professional Development; the training of caregivers in Early Childhood Development (ECD) and the distribution of ECD kits; and the training of parent teacher associations on school management. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
